  "title": "Commodore 64 Classic Platform Stack",
  "body": "# Commodore 64 Classic Platform Stack\n\n**Platform stack:** `retro_c64` · **Era:** 1982–1994 · **Vendor:** Commodore · **Count:** 339\n\nClassic **breadbin C64** — MOS **6510**, **VIC-II**, **SID** (6581/8580), dual **CIA** 6526. Queen CHIPS scaffold; **not** the 2025 FPGA C64 Ultimate.\n\n## Stack doctrine\n\nThis page lists every combinatorics leaf stamped `platform_stack: retro_c64` plus companion dies emitted from `field-cpu-companion-seed.json`. Host and guest CPUs matching the stack's `match` rules receive `always_with` linkage at combinatorics build — no manual wiring.\n\n## Manufacturing notes — companion dies\n\n- **MOS 6510** (MOS, 8-bit) — C64 CPU — 6502 derivative with integrated I/O\n- **MOS 6581 SID** (MOS, 8-bit) — 3-voice analog synth — early C64 boards\n- **MOS 8580 SID** (MOS, 8-bit) — 8580 SID — later C64 boards\n- **MOS VIC-II** (MOS, 8-bit) — VIC-II video — 40×25 text, sprites\n- **MOS 6526 CIA1** (MOS, 8-bit) — Keyboard + joystick matrix\n- **MOS 6526 CIA2** (MOS, 8-bit) — Serial + user port\n\n## Catalog ids\n\nThe `chip_ids` array holds all **339** entries for this platform stack, sorted alphabetically. Run `field-ironclad-chips-combinatorics.py combinatronic` for path percents and imprint renders.\n\n*Stack: retro_c64 · seed: data/field-cpu-companion-seed.json · citation: ironclad:chips:3*",
